# Portfolio CSS Integration Plan

The goal is to style the existing HTML portfolio, add a pure CSS dark mode toggle, adjust the structure to support responsive project cards, and prepare the project in a new folder/repository named `my-css-portfolio` for Vercel deployment.

## User Review Required
None of these changes are breaking, but review is required to ensure the design direction (pure HTML/CSS, "Checkbox Hack" for dark mode) matches expectations before proceeding.

## Proposed Changes

### Setup and Configuration
- **Create New Directory**: I will copy your files to a new directory called `c:\Users\USER\Documents\GitHub\my-css-portfolio` as required by the activity guidelines. 

### HTML Refactoring
#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/USER/Documents/GitHub/my_html_porfolio/index.html)
- **Dark Mode Checkbox**: Insert `<input type="checkbox" id="dark-mode" class="dark-mode-checkbox">` and its `<label>` at the top of the body.
- **Structure Cleanup**: 
    - Wrap the main content in a `.app-container` so the checkbox hack can easily target and change CSS variables for the whole page.
    - Fix the `.projects-container` so that instead of multiple `<section id="ProjectsId">`, there is one `<section id="projects">` containing a CSS Grid or Flexbox of `<article class="project-card">`s.
- **Link Text**: Change links to say "View Code" (for GitHub) and "Live Demo" (for Vercel).

### Style Implementation
#### [NEW] `style.css`
- **Variables**: Define `--bg-color`, `--text-color`, `--card-bg`, `--accent-color` on `:root` and change them on `.dark-mode-checkbox:checked ~ .app-container`.
- **Layout**: Implement a clean, responsive layout loosely inspired by modern design principles with rich aesthetics.
- **Cards**: Style projects as cards with hover effects.
- **Responsiveness**: Use `@media` queries to ensure mobile-friendliness.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- You can test the newly designed layout and the dark mode switch by opening `c:\Users\USER\Documents\GitHub\my-css-portfolio\index.html` in your browser.
- Once completed, I will provide the steps required for you to host it live on Vercel.
